{"word":"ξένη","slug":"ξένη","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ξένη</b></el> <el>(ξένη, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> of <el>ξένος</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a female guest: a foreign woman</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>(<a href='S:subaudi, subaudito'>sub.</a> <el>γῆ</el>), <i>a foreign country</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}